			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>A few weeks ago, on 18th June 2010, a brand new radio station took to the air.</p>
<p>Gaydio, based in Manchester, is an FM station aimed at and run by Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual and Trans People.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s not the world&#8217;s first such station. There are established FM stations in <a href="http://www.joy.org.au/" title="Joy FM" target="_blank">Australia</a> and <a href="http://www.proudfm.com/" title="Proud FM" target="_blank">Toronto</a>, for instance plus <a href="http://radiotime.com/genre/c_240/Gay.aspx" title="Joy FM" target="_blank">a host of internet stations</a></p>
<p>Unlike many, Gaydio is not simply a music station though; it&#8217;s aimed at a wider than usual audience, and has a community development dimension too.</p>
<p>To find out more I spoke to one of the founding directors, Toby Whitehouse, at the studios in central Manchester.</p>
<p><i>You can listen to the station online at <a href="http://www.gaydio.co.uk" title="Gaydio Website" target="_blank">http://www.gaydio.co.uk</a></i></p>
]]></content:encoded>
