			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Earlier this week I interviewed veteran Human Rights campaigner Peter Tatchell about what makes him tick, his methods and some of his opinions. You can hear that interview in the preceding item.</p>
<p>Peter and I were both speaking at the Centre for Local Policy Studies Summer School at Crewe Hall in Cheshire. In his keynote speech he addressed the risk that in being blindly sensitive to &#8220;multiculturalism&#8221; we might undermine everyone&#8217;s human rights - including sections of the cultures we are reticent to challenge. Is female genital mutilation an absolute violation or subject to cultural relativism, for instance.</p>
<p>Here is an excerpt from the opening section of Peter&#8217;s overall 30 minute presentation. I may make further segments available if the demand appears to be there.</p>
<p>



